<subSubSection id="69D96AEAB40BFF9A649DF1A0FB8B89A3" pageId="55" pageNumber="56" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="217C3961B40BFF9A649DF1A0FED88A8A" blockId="55.[151,1437,150,645]" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">
<emphasis id="13B7E573B40BFF9A649DF1A0FEFC8B96" bold="true" box="[199,315,150,176]" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="E6C342E2B40BFF9A6518F1A0FE188B96" authority="Rosa &amp; Aswathi &amp; Bijoy, 2021" authorityName="Rosa &amp; Aswathi &amp; Bijoy" authorityYear="2021" box="[322,479,150,176]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Chrysis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="55" pageNumber="56" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="polita" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="13B7E573B40BFF9A6518F1A0FE188B96" box="[322,479,150,176]" italics="true" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">Chrysis polita</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="13B7E573B40BFF9A65BCF1A0FDF88B96" bold="true" box="[486,575,150,176]" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="08845808B40BFF9A65BCF1A0FDF88B96" box="[486,575,150,176]" pageId="55" pageNumber="56" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
belongs to the 
<taxonomicName id="E6C342E2B40BFF9A66B3F1A0FC9F8B96" baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityYear="1758" box="[745,856,150,176]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Chrysis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="55" pageNumber="56" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ignita">
<emphasis id="13B7E573B40BFF9A66B3F1A0FC9F8B96" box="[745,856,150,176]" italics="true" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">Ch. ignita</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species group. It is related to 
<taxonomicName id="E6C342E2B40BFF9A60FCF1A0FAFC8B96" authorityName="Linsenmaier" authorityYear="1959" box="[1190,1339,150,176]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Chrysis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="55" pageNumber="56" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="castigata">
<emphasis id="13B7E573B40BFF9A60FCF1A0FAFC8B96" box="[1190,1339,150,176]" italics="true" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">Ch. castigata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="E6C342E2B40BFF9A6113F1A0FE198BF2" authority="du Buysson, 1898 a" authorityName="du Buysson" authorityYear="1898" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Chrysis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="55" pageNumber="56" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="immaculata">
<emphasis id="13B7E573B40BFF9A6113F1A0FF388BF2" italics="true" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">Ch. immaculata</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="45524490B40BFF9A655CF18CFE198BF2" author="du Buysson, R." box="[262,478,186,213]" pageId="55" pageNumber="56" pagination="125 - 147" refId="ref51482" refString="du Buysson, R. (1898 a) Contribution aux Chrysides du Globe (3 e serie). Revue d'Entomologie, 17, 125 - 147." type="journal article" year="1898">du Buysson, 1898a</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="E6C342E2B40BFF9A6642F18CFC998BF3" authority="Dahlbom, 1854" authorityName="Dahlbom" authorityYear="1854" box="[536,862,186,213]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Chrysis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="55" pageNumber="56" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="exsulans">
<emphasis id="13B7E573B40BFF9A6642F18CFD618BF2" box="[536,678,186,212]" italics="true" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">Ch. exsulans</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="45524490B40BFF9A66F7F18CFC998BF3" author="Dahlbom, A. G." box="[685,862,186,213]" pageId="55" pageNumber="56" refId="ref51020" refString="Dahlbom, A. G. (1854) Hymenoptera Europaea praecipue borealia, formis typicis nonnullis specierum generumve exoticorum propter nexum systematicum associatis, per familias, genera, species et varietates disposita atque descripta. Tomus secundus. Chrysis in sensu Linnaeano. Friedrich Nicolai, Berolini [Berlin], xxiv + 412 pp., 12 pls. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 15890" type="book" year="1854">Dahlbom, 1854</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, for general habitus, genitalia and colouration, with tergum I blue, contrasting with the other two red metasomal terga. 
<taxonomicName id="E6C342E2B40BFF9A67D4F1E8FBEA8BDE" authority="Rosa &amp; Aswathi &amp; Bijoy, 2021" authorityName="Rosa &amp; Aswathi &amp; Bijoy" authorityYear="2021" box="[910,1069,222,248]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Chrysis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="55" pageNumber="56" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="polita" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="13B7E573B40BFF9A67D4F1E8FBEA8BDE" box="[910,1069,222,248]" italics="true" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">Chrysis polita</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="13B7E573B40BFF9A606FF1E8FB578BDE" bold="true" box="[1077,1168,222,248]" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="08845808B40BFF9A606FF1E8FB578BDE" box="[1077,1168,222,248]" pageId="55" pageNumber="56" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
can be easily separated from other similar species for the scattered punctation of the metasomal tergum II (
<figureCitation id="B9F825E4B40BFF9A601EF034FB6C8A3B" box="[1092,1195,258,285]" captionStart="FIGURE 51" captionStartId="54.[151,250,1950,1974]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,993,1924]" captionTargetId="figure-375@54.[151,1436,993,1927]" captionTargetPageId="54" captionText="FIGURE 51. Chrysis metasoma, dorsal view, and genital capsule. A, E. Chrysis polita Rosa, sp. nov. B, F. Chrysis exsulans Dahlbom, 1844. C, G. Chrysis castigata Linsenmaier, 1959. D, H. Chrysis immaculata du Buysson, 1898. Scale bars 1.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4544702" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4544702/files/figure.png" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">Fig. 51A</figureCitation>
) and for the shape of the genital capsule (
<figureCitation id="B9F825E4B40BFF9A652DF010FE1B8A67" box="[375,476,294,321]" captionStart="FIGURE 51" captionStartId="54.[151,250,1950,1974]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,993,1924]" captionTargetId="figure-375@54.[151,1436,993,1927]" captionTargetPageId="54" captionText="FIGURE 51. Chrysis metasoma, dorsal view, and genital capsule. A, E. Chrysis polita Rosa, sp. nov. B, F. Chrysis exsulans Dahlbom, 1844. C, G. Chrysis castigata Linsenmaier, 1959. D, H. Chrysis immaculata du Buysson, 1898. Scale bars 1.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4544702" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4544702/files/figure.png" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">Fig. 51E</figureCitation>
); moreover, it is separated from 
<taxonomicName id="E6C342E2B40BFF9A671CF010FC1C8A66" authorityName="Linsenmaier" authorityYear="1959" box="[838,987,294,320]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Chrysis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="55" pageNumber="56" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="castigata">
<emphasis id="13B7E573B40BFF9A671CF010FC1C8A66" box="[838,987,294,320]" italics="true" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">Ch. castigata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="E6C342E2B40BFF9A604BF010FB038A66" authorityName="du Buysson" authorityYear="1898" box="[1041,1220,294,320]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Chrysis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="55" pageNumber="56" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="immaculata">
<emphasis id="13B7E573B40BFF9A604BF010FB038A66" box="[1041,1220,294,320]" italics="true" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">Ch. immaculata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by different colour pattern of the tergum I, which is apically red to golden red, whereas it is fully blue in 
<taxonomicName id="E6C342E2B40BFF9A6033F07CFB1D8A42" authority="Rosa &amp; Aswathi &amp; Bijoy, 2021" authorityName="Rosa &amp; Aswathi &amp; Bijoy" authorityYear="2021" box="[1129,1242,330,356]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Chrysis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="55" pageNumber="56" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="polita" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="13B7E573B40BFF9A6033F07CFB1D8A42" box="[1129,1242,330,356]" italics="true" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">Ch. polita</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="13B7E573B40BFF9A60B8F07CFAFA8A42" bold="true" box="[1250,1341,330,356]" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="08845808B40BFF9A60B8F07CFAFA8A42" box="[1250,1341,330,356]" pageId="55" pageNumber="56" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
Besides different punctation and genitalia, it is separated from 
<taxonomicName id="E6C342E2B40BFF9A6750F058FC0E8AAE" authorityName="Dahlbom" authorityYear="1854" box="[778,969,366,392]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Chrysis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="55" pageNumber="56" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="exsulans">
<emphasis id="13B7E573B40BFF9A6750F058FC0E8AAE" box="[778,969,366,392]" italics="true" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">Chrysis exsulans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by different shape of tergum III, and its apical teeth.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="217C3961B40BFF9A649DF080FB8B89A3" blockId="55.[151,1437,150,645]" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">
Another two species have contrasting blue tergum I, the females of 
<taxonomicName id="E6C342E2B40BFF9A678EF080FAFD8AF6" authority="Linnaeus, 1761" authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1761" box="[980,1338,438,464]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Chrysis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="55" pageNumber="56" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fulgida">
<emphasis id="13B7E573B40BFF9A678EF080FB468AF6" box="[980,1153,438,464]" italics="true" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">Chrysis fulgida</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="45524490B40BFF9A60D1F080FAFD8AF6" author="Linnaeus, C." box="[1163,1338,438,464]" pageId="55" pageNumber="56" refId="ref53393" refString="Linnaeus, C. (1761) Fauna Svecica sistens Animalia Sveciae Regni: Mammalia, Aves, Amphibia, Pisces, Insecta, Vermes. Distributa per Classes et Ordines, Genera et Species, cum Differentiis, Specierum, Synonymis, Auctorum, Nominibus Incolarum, Locis natalium, Descriptionibus Insectorum. Editio Altera, Auctior. Laurentius Salvius, Stockholmiae, 578 pp., 2 pls. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 46380" type="book" year="1761">Linnaeus, 1761</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="E6C342E2B40BFF9A612FF080FE778AD3" authority="Tsuneki, 1952" authorityName="Tsuneki" authorityYear="1952" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Chrysis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="55" pageNumber="56" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fulgidaria">
<emphasis id="13B7E573B40BFF9A612FF080FEC08AD2" italics="true" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">Ch. fulgidaria</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="45524490B40BFF9A6554F0ECFE778AD3" author="Tsuneki, K." box="[270,432,474,501]" pageId="55" pageNumber="56" pagination="31 - 33" refId="ref57509" refString="Tsuneki, K. (1952) Two new species of Chrysididae from Japan and Korea. Insecta Matsumurana, 18 (1 - 2), 31 - 33." type="journal article" year="1952">Tsuneki, 1952</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. The first is a relatively common species in the Palaearctic region but genetically belongs to a different subgroup, together with 
<taxonomicName id="E6C342E2B40BFF9A6616F0C8FCFF893E" authority="Christ, 1791" authorityName="Christ" authorityYear="1791" box="[588,824,510,536]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Chrysis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="55" pageNumber="56" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="iris">
<emphasis id="13B7E573B40BFF9A6616F0C8FD65893E" box="[588,674,510,536]" italics="true" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">Ch. iris</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="45524490B40BFF9A66F6F0C8FCFF893E" author="Christ, J. L." box="[684,824,510,536]" pageId="55" pageNumber="56" refId="ref50781" refString="Christ, J. L. (1791) Naturgeschichte, Klassification und Nomenclatur der Insekten vom Bienen, Wespen und Ameisengeschlecht: als der funften Klasse funfte Ordnung des Linneischen Natursystems von den Insekten, Hymenoptera: mit hautigen Flugeln. Hermannischer Buchhandlung, Frankfurt am Main, 535 pp., 60 pls." type="book" year="1791">Christ, 1791</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation id="45524490B40BFF9A6713F0C8FBCA893E" author="Pauli, T. &amp; Castillo-Cajas, R. F. &amp; Rosa, P. &amp; Kukowka, S. &amp; Berg, A. &amp; van den Berghe, E. &amp; Fornoff, F. &amp; Hopfenmuller, S. &amp; Niehuis, M. &amp; Peters, R. S. &amp; Staab, M. &amp; Strumia, F. &amp; Tischendorf, S. &amp; Schmitt, F. &amp; Niehuis, O." box="[841,1037,510,536]" pageId="55" pageNumber="56" pagination="322 - 335" refId="ref54423" refString="Pauli, T., Castillo-Cajas, R. F., Rosa, P., Kukowka, S., Berg, A., van den Berghe, E., Fornoff, F., Hopfenmuller, S., Niehuis, M., Peters, R. S., Staab, M., Strumia, F., Tischendorf, S., Schmitt, F. &amp; Niehuis, O. (2019) Phylogenetic analysis of cuckoo wasps (Chrysididae) reveals the partially artificial nature of the current classification at the genus level in this family of Hymenoptera. Systematic Entomology, 44 (2), 322 - 335. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / syen. 12323" type="journal article" year="2019">
Pauli 
<emphasis id="13B7E573B40BFF9A67D7F0C9FC0F893E" box="[909,968,510,536]" italics="true" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">et al.</emphasis>
2019
</bibRefCitation>
); besides the morphological differences, the male of 
<taxonomicName id="E6C342E2B40BFF9A652BF314FE36891A" authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1761" box="[369,497,546,572]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Chrysis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="55" pageNumber="56" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fulgida">
<emphasis id="13B7E573B40BFF9A652BF314FE36891A" box="[369,497,546,572]" italics="true" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">Ch. fulgida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is also differently coloured, having a large blue dorsal spot on tergum II. 
<taxonomicName id="E6C342E2B40BFF9A611DF314FEC08946" authorityName="Tsuneki" authorityYear="1952" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Chrysis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="55" pageNumber="56" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fulgidaria">
<emphasis id="13B7E573B40BFF9A611DF314FEC08946" italics="true" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">Chrysis fulgidaria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was described on a single female Korean specimen, and it can be easily separated from 
<taxonomicName id="E6C342E2B40BFF9A6095F370FAF98946" authority="Rosa &amp; Aswathi &amp; Bijoy, 2021" authorityName="Rosa &amp; Aswathi &amp; Bijoy" authorityYear="2021" box="[1231,1342,582,608]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Chrysis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="55" pageNumber="56" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="polita" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="13B7E573B40BFF9A6095F370FAF98946" box="[1231,1342,582,608]" italics="true" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">Ch. polita</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="13B7E573B40BFF9A611EF370FA5B8946" bold="true" box="[1348,1436,582,608]" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="08845808B40BFF9A611EF370FA5B8946" box="[1348,1436,582,608]" pageId="55" pageNumber="56" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
by dense metasomal punctation and narrow and spine-like apical teeth on tergum III.
</paragraph>
